@end menu

@node Core directories
@subsection Core directories

@vindex paths-dir-root
@vindex paths-dir-downloads
@vindex paths-dir-system-apps
@vindex paths-dir-dropbox
@vindex paths-dir-google-drive
@vindex paths-dir-emacs
@vindex paths-dir-emacs-profiles
The following variables define the top-level directories from which most other paths derive:

@itemize
@item
@code{paths-dir-root} (default: @samp{"/"}): the filesystem root.
@item
@code{paths-dir-downloads} (default: @samp{~/Downloads/}): the system downloads directory.
@item
@code{paths-dir-system-apps} (default: @samp{/Applications/}): the macOS applications directory.
@item
@code{paths-dir-dropbox} (default: @samp{~/Library/CloudStorage/Dropbox/}): the Dropbox sync directory. Many personal data directories are children of this path.
@item
@code{paths-dir-google-drive} (default: @samp{~/My Drive/}): the Google Drive sync directory. Library and media directories are children of this path.
@item
@code{paths-dir-emacs} (default: @code{user-emacs-directory}): the Emacs configuration directory.
@item
@code{paths-dir-emacs-profiles} (default: @samp{~/.config/emacs-profiles/}): the directory containing multiple Emacs profiles.
@end itemize

@node Dropbox directories
@subsection Dropbox directories

@vindex paths-dir-dotfiles
@vindex paths-dir-dotemacs
@vindex paths-dir-notes
@vindex paths-dir-journal
