@vindex paths-file-metaculus
@vindex paths-file-fm
@vindex paths-file-ean
@vindex paths-file-work
@vindex paths-file-tlon
These variables point to individual Org files used for task management, knowledge capture, and project tracking. Notable entries include:

@itemize
@item
@code{paths-file-notes} (@samp{notes/notes.org}): the main notes file.
@item
@code{paths-file-inbox-desktop} and @code{paths-file-inbox-mobile}: capture inboxes for desktop and mobile.
@item
@code{paths-file-calendar} (@samp{android/calendar.org}): the calendar file synced with a mobile device.
@item
@code{paths-file-anki} (@samp{anki/main.org}): the Anki flashcard source file.
@item
@code{paths-file-config} (@samp{emacs/config.org}): the literate Emacs configuration.
@item
@code{paths-file-karabiner}: the Karabiner keyboard customization file in Org format.
@item
@code{paths-file-work}: the work dashboard.
@end itemize

@node Bibliography files
@subsection Bibliography files

@vindex paths-file-personal-bibliography-old
@vindex paths-file-personal-bibliography-new
@vindex paths-files-bibliography-personal
@vindex paths-files-bibliography-all
The bibliography variables define Bib@TeX{} database files:

@itemize
@item
@code{paths-file-personal-bibliography-new} (@samp{new.bib}) and @code{paths-file-personal-bibliography-old} (@samp{old.bib}): the active and legacy bibliography files.
@item
@code{paths-files-bibliography-personal}: a list containing both personal bibliography files, suitable for passing to @samp{ebib} or @samp{citar}.
@item
@code{paths-files-bibliography-all}: a list of all bibliography files, including both personal and organization files. Defaults to an empty list; organization packages append their files at load time.
@end itemize

